Tailwind CSS v4.2.4 — this uses the new v4 PostCSS plugin `@tailwindcss/postcss` instead of the old `tailwindcss` plugin. The postcss.config.js needs to be updated.

In Tailwind CSS v4, the postcss config should use `@tailwindcss/postcss` instead of `tailwindcss`:

```js
export default {
  plugins: {
    "@tailwindcss/postcss": {},
  },
}
```

Also, autoprefixer is not needed separately in v4 since it's built into the Tailwind CSS v4 PostCSS plugin.

Also, the CSS file should be checked — v4 uses `@import "tailwindcss"` instead of `@tailwind base/components/utilities`.

Let me check the CSS file as well.

